description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 Cancer and Aseptic Services Pharmacist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a knowledgeable and enthusiastic pharmacist to join our aseptic services team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Our aseptic services pharmacists work across Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust at the Charing Cross and Hammersmith Hospital sites, offering a wealth of expertise to the oncology, haematology, research and nutrition teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our two aseptic units are staffed by enthusiastic and committed teams delivering a high number of doses daily across both sites to various specialities, including our rapidly expanding BMT unit, and one of only three gestational trophoblastic disease centres nationwide. You would&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Play an active role in the day to day running of our aseptic units&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with a wide range of healthcare professionals to ensure SACT is prescribed safely and efficaciously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Screen SACT prescriptions for oncology, haematology, clinical trials and BMT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become familiar with the ARIA e-prescribing system; supporting prescribers, nurses and pharmacy staff with its use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with dieticians and the nutrition MDT; ordering and screening parenteral nutrition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively support foundation and practice level band 6 pharmacists carrying out the PG Diploma in General Pharmacy Practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide cover for the Lead Pharmacist, Aseptic Services as requested&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should have excellent organisational and communication skills and be happy to work independently or in a team. Applicants need significant post-registration training and experience in Hospital Pharmacy including previous experience in at least one of the relevant areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rosie Webb on 020 331 17398&lt;/p&gt;
